- A flight duration of 300 minutes is equivalent to 5 hours.

- A "quarter of an hour" refers to 15 minutes;
- "Soar above the average journey length" means the average flight distance is greater than the overall average flight distance in the flight history;
- "Typically travel" refers to the average flight distance.

- 'Captains of vast fleets of ships' refers to airlines;
- 'Ships' refers to flights;
